<Defs>
	<ThingDef ParentName="RVFFA_BaseArmor">
		<defName>RVFFA_ScoutArmor</defName>
		<label>Illuminate Scout Armor</label>
		<description>A set of sleek Avali scout armour. Covering nearly their entire body barring their head and tail, this suit brings true scouting capabilities to the table. Whilst not as protective as other armours, it does increase the wearer’s speed with the help of its exo-skeleton. Allowing for better evasion of enemies or perhaps a more rapid approach with a close ranged weapon.</description>
		<graphicData>
			<texPath>RimValiFFA/Things/Apparel/ScoutArmor/ScoutArmor_RVFFA_Avali_south</texPath>
		</graphicData>
		<recipeMaker>
			<skillRequirements>
				<Crafting>5</Crafting>
			</skillRequirements>
		</recipeMaker>
		<statBases>
			<WorkToMake>30000</WorkToMake>
			<MaxHitPoints>900</MaxHitPoints>
			<Mass>1.5</Mass>
			<Flammability>0.02</Flammability>
			<ArmorRating_Sharp>0.7</ArmorRating_Sharp>
			<ArmorRating_Blunt>0.6</ArmorRating_Blunt>
			<ArmorRating_Heat>0.2</ArmorRating_Heat>
			<Insulation_Cold>4</Insulation_Cold>
			<Insulation_Heat>6</Insulation_Heat>
			<EquipDelay>2</EquipDelay>
		</statBases>
		<costList>
			<ComponentIndustrial>5</ComponentIndustrial>
			<ComponentSpacer>2</ComponentSpacer>
			<Plasteel>20</Plasteel>
			<RVFFA_Ferrogel>10</RVFFA_Ferrogel>
		</costList>
		<apparel>
			<tags>
				<li>RVFFA_ScoutGear</li>
			</tags>
			<wornGraphicPath>RimValiFFA/Things/Apparel/ScoutArmor/ScoutArmor</wornGraphicPath>
		</apparel>
		<recipeMaker>
			<researchPrerequisite>RVFFA_ScoutingTech</researchPrerequisite>
		</recipeMaker>
	</ThingDef>

	<ThingDef ParentName="RVFFA_BaseArmorHelmet">
		<defName>RVFFA_ScoutHelment</defName>
		<label>Illuminate Scout Helmet</label>
		<description>A light Avali scout helmet. Going on their head and barely protecting the ears, this piece of headwear is commonly paired with the rest of the suit. Giving the same protections as the rest of the suit, it in turn also features an antenna that allows them to communicate with homebase, sometimes even allowing them to receive information about the target they’re shooting at.</description>
